  "prompt": "International awards of Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shahrukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has received numerous international awards and honors throughout his career for his contributions to the entertainment industry. Some of the notable international awards and recognitions include:\n\n1. **Legion of Honour** (2014) - France's highest civilian award was presented to him for his contribution to cinema.\n\n2. **UNESCO Pyramid con Marni Award** (2011) - He received this award for his charitable work and dedication to education.\n\n3. **Crystal Award** (2018) - Presented by the World Economic Forum for Khan's leadership in championing children's and women's rights in India.\n\n4. **Outstanding Contribution to Cinema Award** - He has been recognized at several international film festivals, including the Marrakech International Film Festival (2012).\n\n5. **Global Icon of the Year** (2018) - Awarded at the Asian Awards.\n\n6. **Datukship** (2008) - An honorary title from the Malaysian government, similar to knighthood.\n\n7. **Honorary Doctorates** - He has received honorary degrees from several international universities, including the University of Edinburgh (2015), in recognition of his philanthropy and global influence.\n\n8. **The Asian Awards, UK** - Recognized in various categories over the years for his outstanding contribution to cinema.\n\nShahrukh Khan is also celebrated at various international platforms and film festivals for his extensive work in Indian cinema and his influence on the global stage. Note that this information might not be exhaustive, and it's always good to check for the most up-to-date achievements.",
